plate is a json templating library that takes in input "templates" and 
a json input along wiht an input file and output file.

Example:

plate \
--template-link='<!--%' \
--input-link='<!--%!' \
--output='out.htm' \
--formatter='html-format' \
--template='
<header>
	<h1><!--%title--></h1>
	<p class="subtitle"><!--%subtitle--></p>
	<hr>
	<p><!--%description--></p>
</header>
' \
--json-data='
{
	"title": "My title!"
	"subtitle": "My subtitle!"
	"description": "this is a basic showcase of plate"
}
' \
 --input='
<head>
	<title>basic test site</title>
</head>
<body>
	<section id="my_content">
		<!--%!values-->
	</section>
</body>
'

After running this out.htm would contain the following:


<head>
	<title>basic test site</title>
</head>
<body>
	<section id="my_content">
		<header>
			<h1>My title!</h1>
			<p class="subtitle">My subtitle!</p>
			<hr>
			<p>this is a basic showcase of plate</p>
		</header>
	</section>
</body>

Plate searchs inside the input file until it comes accross a line with the "input link" delimiter
which tells plate to start writing data from the given template, the template file is read for a
unique "template link" delimiter, when a link is found it will be replaced with its contense inside
of a json file provided. This project was used to automate data display on my static website which 
preloads all its data from the github api before using plate to properly display said data onto the 
page. 

https://x3hy.github.io
